tary training in Toronto. Beginning with the formation of a student rifle company in 1861, and focussing on the story of the COTC from 1914 to 1968, author Eric McGeer seeks to enlarge appreciation of the university’s remarkable contribution to the defence of Canada, the place of military education in an academic setting, and the experience of the students who embodied the ideal of service to alma mater and to country.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aEducation, HigherzOntariozTorontoxHistoryy20th century. 0aMilitary educationzOntariozTorontoxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Military / Canada.2bisacsh  aCanada.  aUniversity of Toronto.  aacademic environment.  aleadership.  amilitary.  aofficer selection and training.  aservice before self.  astudent life and attitudes.  atraining.  auniversity at war.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751810340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487518103423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487518103.jpg  a978-3-11-061017-8  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065206-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSH